-- Greek debt crisis creates "headwind": White House
-- 
-- Mon Jun 20, 2011 2:26pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2011/06/20/us-eurozone-whitehouse-idUSTRE75J5NF20110620

 

 WASHINGTON  (Reuters) - The Greek debt crisis creates "headwind" for the global economy, but the United States believes Europe can work with Greece to resolve it, White House spokesman Jay Carney said on Monday. 

 Euro zone finance ministers gave Greece two weeks from Monday to approve stricter austerity measures in return for another 12 billion euros in emergency loans, increasing pressure on Athens to get its ragged finances in order. (Reporting by  Matt Spetalnick ; Editing by  Will Dunham )